@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Manifesto";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Our Manifesto</h1>
        <p class="lead">Why CraftPledge exists, in our own words.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="manifesto-text">

            <p class="pull-quote">We believe in the human behind the work.</p>

            <p>Behind every great piece of work, there is a person. Someone who learned, practised, failed, and tried again. Someone who brought their lived experience, their culture, their imperfections, and their soul to what they made.</p>

            <p>That matters. It has always mattered. And in an age where machines can generate words, images, music, and code in seconds &mdash; it matters more than ever.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">This is not a war against technology.</h2>

            <p>We are not Luddites. We are not afraid of progress. Technology has always been a partner to human creativity &mdash; from the printing press to the piano, from the camera to the compiler.</p>

            <p class="pull-quote">But there is a line.</p>

            <p>There is a difference between a tool that empowers a human and a system that replaces one. Between a craftsperson who uses a power drill and a factory that removes the craftsperson entirely.</p>

            <p>We believe that line should be visible. And we believe you have the right to know which side of it your products and services fall on.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">The problem is simple.</h2>

            <p class="pull-quote">You cannot tell anymore.</p>

            <p>You cannot tell if the article you read was written by a journalist who spent weeks investigating, or generated in four seconds. You cannot tell if the logo on your product was designed by someone who understood your brand, or assembled by an algorithm that understood your prompt. You cannot tell if the code running your business was architected by an engineer who considered the edge cases, or autocompleted by a model that statistically guessed the next token.</p>

            <p>The craft is becoming invisible. Not because it has disappeared &mdash; but because it has become indistinguishable from its imitation.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">Our pledge.</h2>

            <p>We pledge to make the human visible again.</p>

            <p>We provide a trusted, verifiable certification that allows creators, businesses, and entire supply chains to demonstrate &mdash; with accountability &mdash; that their work is genuinely human-made.</p>

            <p class="pull-quote">When you see the CraftPledge mark, you know: A real person made this. They stand behind that claim. It has been verified.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">A movement, not a moment.</h2>

            <p>CraftPledge is not a reaction to a trend. It is an answer to a permanent shift.</p>

            <p>AI is not going away. It will get better, faster, cheaper, and more convincing. The gap between human-made and machine-generated will narrow until it is invisible to the untrained eye.</p>

            <p class="pull-quote">But it will never be invisible to the heart.</p>

            <p>There will always be people who care about who made something. Who want to support human livelihoods, human expression, human mastery. Who believe that the story behind the work is part of the work itself.</p>

            <p>Those people deserve a mark they can trust. That mark is CraftPledge.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Stand behind your craft</h2>
        <p>Join the movement of creators and businesses who believe human work deserves to be recognised.</p>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Tiers" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Explore the Pledge Tiers</a>
    </div>
</section>
